  "prompt": "You push backward against the ground to move a skateboard forward. The force you make acts against the ground. What force acts against you to move you forward?",
  "response": "When you push backward against the ground with your foot to move a skateboard forward, the force you exert on the ground is called the **action force**. According to **Newton's Third Law of Motion**, the ground exerts an equal and opposite force on you, called the **reaction force**. \n\nThis reaction force acts on you and the skateboard, propelling you forward. In this case, the reaction force is the **frictional force** between your foot and the ground, which pushes you in the opposite direction of your action force, allowing you to move forward.",
